</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1917,2016]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,153,251]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="561" pageId="3" pageNumber="560">
This genus includes 24 species, of which one is a fossil, and two or more Asian species are known only from descriptions (
<bibRefCitation accessDate="2019-05-01" author="ThripsWiki" box="[277,477,1953,1979]" pageId="3" pageNumber="560" publicationUrl="http://thrips.info/wiki/" refId="ref7542" refString="ThripsWiki (2019) providing information on the World's thrips. Available from: http: // thrips. info / wiki / (accessed 1 May 2019)" title="providing information on the World's thrips" type="url" year="2019">ThripsWiki 2019</bibRefCitation>
). The species listed in this genus were described from many parts of the world, but their systematic relationships have never been examined, and there is no satisfactory generic diagnosis. In particular, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Haliday" box="[151,296,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Phlaeothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,296,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="561">Phlaeothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not clearly distinguished from the much larger genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hood" authorityYear="1912" box="[926,1113,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplandrothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[926,1113,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="561">Hoplandrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Haliday" authorityName="Haliday" authorityYear="1836" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Phlaeothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceus">
<emphasis box="[1127,1387,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="561">Phlaeothrips coriaceus</emphasis>
Haliday
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[260,308,189,215]" pageId="4" pageNumber="561">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, is widespread across Europe, reported from California (
<bibRefCitation author="Hoddle" box="[1171,1382,189,215]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hoddle" pageId="4" pageNumber="561" refId="ref6313" refString="Hoddle, M., Mound, L. A. &amp; Paris, D. (2019) Thysanoptera Californica. An identification and information system to thrips in California. Available from: https: // keys. lucidcentral. org / keys / v 3 / thrips _ of _ california _ 2019 / (accessed 10 July 2019)" type="url" year="2019">
Hoddle 
<emphasis box="[1262,1310,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="561">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
) and recorded from north of 
<collectingCountry box="[414,459,225,251]" name="Iran" pageId="4" pageNumber="561">Iran</collectingCountry>
based on two females beaten from shrubs (zur 
<bibRefCitation author="Strassen, R." box="[989,1150,225,251]" journalOrPublisher="Thysanoptera, Thrips" pageId="4" pageNumber="561" pagination="11 - 14" part="2" refId="ref7657" refString="zur Strassen, R. (2003) Records of some Thysanoptera from Iran. Thysanoptera, Thrips, 2, 11 - 14." title="Records of some Thysanoptera from Iran" type="journal article" year="2003">Strassen 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
